version: 1.3.1

## Changelog

### 1.3.1 (2026-04-16)
- Fix: PostToolUse GPU release hook (ammo-gpu-release.sh) was silently dropping releases — two regex bugs reproduced and fixed:
  - Pre-filter `(?<!\S)gpu_reservation\.py` rejected path-prefixed invocations (`python .claude/.../gpu_reservation.py reserve …`), so the hook never even attempted release for the canonical pattern. Pre-filter now matches regardless of path prefix.
  - Session-id extractor `\S+` captured trailing `)` from `$(reserve … --session-id foo)` and returned empty for `--session-id=foo`, both causing release to target the wrong id. Replaced with bounded char class `[A-Za-z0-9_.\-]+` and `--session-id[=\s]` boundary.
  - Adds `/tmp/ammo_gpu_res/release.log` audit trail for every release attempt so future leak investigations can distinguish "hook never fired" from "hook fired but extraction missed the id".
- Fix: lease_hours default lowered from 2h → 15min (0.25h) in gpu_reservation.py at all three sites (write_reservation, reserve, argparse). Long sweeps/nsys must now pass `--lease-hours 2` explicitly. Self-heals a dropped release within 15 minutes instead of 2 hours.
- Feat: SubagentStop hook (ammo-subagent-release.sh) — wired in settings.local.json as a safety net that releases `$CLAUDE_SESSION_ID` and `$CLAUDE_SESSION_ID:$AGENT_ID` when a subagent returns. Does not touch sibling subagents' reservations.
- Docs: gpu-pool.md now documents (a) 15-min default lease, (b) `--lease-hours 2` for long sweeps/nsys, (c) session-id character rules (`[A-Za-z0-9_.\-]`), (d) explicit `release-session` pattern. Removed incorrect "4-hour lease automatic" claim from ammo-researcher.md.
- Tests: new `test-ammo-gpu-release.sh` harness validates 5 real-world command forms (canonical $()-wrapped space-form, trailing-paren, equals-form, retry-loop, non-reserve).

